# Implementation Plan - Scrollytelling Feature Section

I will replace the static product grid with a sophisticated scroll-driven experience. The new section will be a tall container that pins the viewport (sticky), allowing users to scroll "through" the features, expanding them one by one.

## Proposed Changes

### HTML
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/hp/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/sona-landing-page/index.html)
- Replace `.card-grid` (and possibly the `.product-intro` wrapper) with a new structure:
    - `.scrolly-features-section` (Total height ~500vh to create scroll space).
    - `.sticky-stage` (Sticky container, 100vh).
    - Inside stage:
        - `.previews-row`: Horizontal flex container of icons/small titles for all 5 features.
        - `.feature-display`: Container for the expanded glass cards.
        - 5 `.feature-card` items, populated with the images and text.

### CSS
#### [MODIFY] [f1.css](file:///c:/Users/hp/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/sona-landing-page/css/f1.css)
- **Scrolly Setup**:
    - `.scrolly-features-section`: `height: 500vh`, `position: relative`.
    - `.sticky-stage`: `position: sticky`, `top: 0`, `height: 100vh`, `display: flex`, `flex-direction: column`.
- **Previews Row**:
    - Placed at the top or bottom. Small opacity when inactive. Active one is highlighted.
- **Feature Cards**:
    - `position: absolute`, `top: 50%`, `left: 50%`.
    - `width: 80%`, `max-width: 900px`.
    - Layout: Grid/Flex with Image Left, Text Right.
    - Style: Glassmorphism (`backdrop-filter`, semi-transparent white/pastel).
    - State:
        - Default: `opacity: 0`, `transform: translate(-50%, -40%) scale(0.9)`.
        - `.active`: `opacity: 1`, `transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1)`.

